You (你) whom I directly address are a person (亻) who is near (尔) me.
Women (女) and children (子) are good (好).

In ancient times, an invitation (请) is most often verbal (讠). 
青 (qīng) hints at the pronunciation of 请 (qǐng).

To ask (问) private questions, she closes the door (门) before she speaks (口). 
The pronunciation of 门 (mén) hints at 问 (wèn).

The top part depicts a pile of soil from an emigrant’s homeland, which she cherishes (贵). 
贝 depicts a shell, which was used as money and was thus valuable (贵).
In ancient matrilineal societies, children inherited the surnames of their mothers (女), who gave them life (生).

The mouth (口) indicates speech, here specifically, asking "what?" 
The radical 尼 (ní) hints at the pronounciation of 呢 (ne).

A sister is a female (女).  
且 (qiě) hints at the pronunciation of 姐 (jiě).
When you are entangled with a rope (丩), you shout (叫) in pain through your mouth (口).

Only humans (人) ask the question "what?" 
十 (shí) accounts for pronouciation.
You use 么 to make a statement less assertive because you only feel a small (厶) amount of certainty about it
When it is dawn (夕), you cannot see others clearly, so you have to call (口) their names (名) to make sure they are who you think they are.
The child (子) studies characters (字) in the school house (宀).
The herd of cows(牛) go in front of (先) the cowboy(儿).
Soil (土) gives birth (生) to plant life.
The plum is the child (子) of the tree (木).
Two friends (朋) chat while each holding a peice of roasted meat(月).
The king has jade (王), which symbolizes his power.
Things that can be done in broad daylight (日) are right (正).  Right things are to be affirmed (是).
The turban (巾) of the commander (= military master) has decorations (一) on it. This shows the commander's (师) mastery of military knowledge.
Mouth (口) hints a spoken question. 马 (mǎ) hints the pronunciation of 吗 (ma).
You say no to what you despise (不).
A child (子) sits under the roof (龸) of a school house to learn.
The snake (也) is greedy by nature, so it wants this and also (也) that.
A country is an enclosure (囗) with an imperial jade (玉) seal in it.
The horn (羊) of a grown-up (大) goat is a beautiful decoration.
In that (那) city (阝) that's far away, men grow long beard. The left part of the character depicts an entangled beard.

fields.explanation_2: where a noun possesses an adjective trait
fields.mnemonic_explanation: When a piece of food is on your spoon (勺), clearly (白) it is yours.
A plank (片) is a thick slice of wood.
Dad is a laboring man (父) who works hard in the field. 巴 (bā) hints the pronunciation of 爸 (bà).
A mother is a woman (女). 马 (mǎ) hints the pronunciation of 妈 (mā).
个 means the count of one (|) person (人).
子 means child. 亥 (hái) provides the pronunciation of 孩 (hái).
You will know who (谁) he is if you talk (讠) to him. 隹 (zhuī) hints at the pronunciation of 谁 (shuí).
To humans, a snake (也) is neither an "I" or a "you," but an "other." "女" indicates that this other is woman.
Men (男)  need strength (力) to work in the field (田).
A younger brother (弟) is lower in order (弟) to his older siblings.
To humans, a snake (也) is neither an "I" or a "you," but an "other." "亻" indicates that this other is a human.
An adult is a big (大) person.
The brother (哥) and the sister are singing (可) to each other.
a person who is drowning in water (氵) flails his hands (又) and then disappears, i.e. becomes nothing
In ancient time, families breed pigs (豕) under the roof (宀) .
There are a few (几) small stools.

fields.explanation_2: When things come together, they are harmonious
fields.mnemonic_explanation: Crops (禾) and mouth (口) are a harmonious (和) pair because grains are consumed through the mouths.

A metropolis (阝) has all (都) the things you want to buy. 者 (zhū) hints at the tone and vowel of 都 (dū).
Of all the single-digit numbers, 9 (九) is the biggest.
